-- Honda to Scrap Conventional Civic as Focus Shifts to Hybrids, Nikkei Says
-- Greg Chang
-- 2010-07-15T17:22:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/honda-to-scrap-conventional-civic-as-focus-shifts-to-hybrids-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             Honda Motor Co. plans to discontinue
development of the conventional gas-powered Civic model for the
Japanese market as it focuses on hybrid vehicles, Nikkei English
News reported, without citing a source for the information.  
 The company also plans to discontinue the Legend sedan and
the Elysion minivan in Japan, according to the report.  
          
          


  


        